      "I'm not sure how to translate `merge({ doc(\"results\").add(newDoc(\"results\")) })` (edit: see solution below) into PHP but it does work like this:\r\n\r\n```php\r\n\\table($table)->get($id)->replace( function($doc) use ($request) {\r\n\t\treturn r\\branch(\r\n\t\t\t$doc->eq(null),\r\n\t\t\t$request,\r\n\t\t\t$doc->merge(array('results' => r\\expr($request['results'])->spliceAt(0, $doc('results'))))\r\n\t\t);\r\n\t}\r\n)->run($conn);\r\n```\r\n\r\n`branch` seems like a bit cleaner syntax.\r\n\r\nEdit: `merge(array('results' => r\\expr($request['results'])->add($doc('results'))))` works"
